@startuml

' Define Actors
:Customer: as customer
:Restaurant Owner: as restaurantOwner

' Define System Boundary
rectangle "OnlineOrder System"{
    (Sign Up) as signup
    (Log in) as login
    (Browse Restaurant) as browse
    (Add to Cart) as addcart
    (Checkout Order) as checkout
    (Register Restaurant) as registerRestaurant
}

' Actor - Use Case Associations
customer -- signup
customer -- login
customer -- browse
customer -- addcart
customer -- checkout

restaurantOwner -- registerRestaurant

addcart .> login : <<include>>
checkout .> login : <<include>>
checkout .> addcart : <<extend>>

' Actor Descriptions
' Customer
note right of customer
**Customer**
The Customer is the primary user of the OnlineOrder system.
Customers can create accounts, browse available restaurants
and their menus, add food items to their shopping cart, and
complete orders through the checkout process. Customers must
be authenticated to access cart and checkout features.
end note

' Restaurant Owner
note left of restaurantOwner
**Restaurant Owner**
The Restaurant Owner is a secondary actor who registers
and manages their restaurant's information in the system.
Owners provide details such as restaurant name, address,
phone number, and menu items with prices and descriptions,
making their restaurant available for customers to browse.
end note

' Sign Up
note bottom of signup
**Sign Up**
Allows new users to create an account in the system by
providing their email, password, first name and last name.
The system validates the email format, ensures the email
is unique, and securely stores the encrypted password.
Upon successful registration, the user can login to access
full system features.
end note

' Login
note bottom of login
**Login**
Enables registered users to authenticate themselves using
their email and password credentials. The system validates
the credentials against stored user data and creates a 
secure session upon successful authentication. This use
case is a prerequisite for accessing protected features like
cart management and checkout.
end note

' Browse Restaurants
note bottom of browse
**Browse Restaurants**
Allows customers to view all available restaurants in the
system with detailed information including name, address,
phone number and restaurant images. Customers can select
a restaurant to view its complete menu with dish details,
prices, descriptions and photos. This helps customers
discover and compare food options.
end note

' Add to Cart
note bottom of addcart
**Add to Cart**
Enables authenticated customers to add selected menu items
to their personal shopping cart. The system validates the
menu item, associates it with the customer's cart, tracks
quantity and automatically calculates the total price.
Customers can add multiple items to build their complete
order. This use case includes Login as authentication is 
required. Checkout Order may extend this use case when
the customer proceeds to finalize their order.
end note

' Checkout Order
note bottom of checkout
**Checkout Order**
Allows customers to finalize their order. The system
displays the order summary with total price, processes
the checkout request, generates an order confirmation,
and returns order details to the customer.Customers may 
arrive here directly (e.g. via "Buy Now" button) or
after adding items to their cart. This use case extends
Add to Cart and requires authentication via Login.
end note

' Register Restaurant
note bottom of registerRestaurant
**Register Restaurant**
Allows restaurant owners to register their establishment
in the system by providing details such as restaurant name,
address, phone number, and menu items with descriptions,
prices, and images. Upon successful registration, the
restaurant becomes available for customers to browse.
end note

@enduml
